---
---
<section class="sr bg-white border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-14 py-20 grid gap-16 items-center" style="grid-template-columns: 380px 1fr;">
    <!-- Photo -->
    <div class="relative">
      <img
        src="/james-casual.jpg"
        alt="James Tannahill"
        class="w-full block"
        style="aspect-ratio:3/4; object-fit:cover; object-position:center top; image-orientation:from-image;"
        loading="lazy"
      />
    </div>
    <!-- Pull quote / statement -->
    <div>
      <p class="text-[9px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase mb-8" style="color:var(--color-amber);">Philosophy</p>
      <blockquote class="font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight mb-8"
                  style="font-family:'NHG Display',sans-serif; font-size:clamp(28px,3.5vw,48px); color:var(--color-ink);">
        "The best businesses are built the same way the best cities are — layer by layer, each system reinforcing the next."
      </blockquote>
      <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.85]" style="color:#666; max-width:480px;">
        James approaches every engagement — investment, advisory, or build — as a systems problem. The question is never what to change. It's what compounding looks like at scale.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
